[31m+ # Build And Toolchain Docs[39m
[31m+[39m
[31m+ This directory holds cross-feature documentation for build orchestration and[39m
[31m+ shared toolchain surfaces.[39m
[31m+[39m
[31m+ For repo-wide entrypoints, start with [`README.md`](../../README.md),[39m
[31m+ [`docs/README.md`](../README.md), and [`GEMINI.md`](../../GEMINI.md). This hub[39m
[31m+ is specifically for shared build, CI, and package-manager workflow guidance.[39m
[31m+[39m
[31m+ ## Open This Hub When[39m
[31m+[39m
[31m+ - you need to know which repo command starts which application surface[39m
[31m+ - you need the right smoke or scanner lane before or after a change[39m
[31m+ - you are touching shared Bazel, Bun, CodeQL, Vercel, or CI wiring[39m
[31m+ - you need the canonical repo validation lanes rather than feature-local tests[39m
[31m+[39m
[31m+ ## Placement Rule[39m
[31m+[39m
[31m+ - Use this directory for repo-wide build and package-manager workflow docs.[39m
[31m+ - Feature-specific build notes should stay with the owning feature docs.[39m
[31m+ - Platform policies that are broader than build orchestration should remain[39m
[31m+   under [`docs/platform/`](../platform/README.md).[39m
